I got my sandwich within a few minutes. All of the hard add ons and take off's were correct. I even got a kickin ranch. I ate my sandwich and left within 5 minutes.  The only thing I did not see inside of this bulding was the soda machine. The bathrooms didn't smell like a bar toilet, the main room didn't have any crumbs on the floor in the middle of the walk way. And the windows are very clear.  The people inside are sandwich makers and everyone is whisking away to make your sandwich as fast as possible. The drive through is constantly moving along. The people sitting outside are calm and content. and the atmosphere is just fine.  The only thing they missed was the Dijon. :)  It didn't drive me up a wall, it didn't make my day any worse. Hell, I didn't even know the Dijon was missing until after I ate it and left! So this place is like any other place. Sometimes you miss a tree in the forest of additives and subtractives. Just like any person in the control tower can lose track of an airplane at any given moment. Just like you at your own job forgetting to place their coffee at their desk instead of leaving it at the break room!  These kids are AWESOME.
